<bug>
    <id>97897</id>
    <title>Recalculate does not always work</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Created attachment 122676
Calc Document with formula</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">1 open attachment</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">2 select cell B3</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">3 press F9 or Extra-Cell-Recalculate</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">4 expected behaviour: the result in B3 changes from 3 to 4</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.6">actual behaviour: formula is not recalculated.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Only when cell A1 or A2 is changed, F9 functions.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Ctrl-Shift-F9 dos function in all cases, problem only exists for F9.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Reproduced in versions 4.4.7, 5.0.4, 5.0.5 and 5.2 (master) on Windows and on Linux.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">The current behaviour is confusing and leads to wrong user-interpretations of formula results.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
